1:1 COMMENT "# io_read_text.z -- one-shot file read, pattern-match the result."
1:66 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `io.read_text` opens a file, slurps its contents into a string, and"
3:70 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# closes. It returns `result(string, ioerror)`:"
4:48 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "#   * `ok`  -- the full file content"
5:37 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "#   * `err` -- an ioerror variant (notfound, permissiondenied, ...)"
6:68 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#"
7:2 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# RAII: the result, the ok-arm string, and any err-arm ioerror payload"
8:71 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# are all freed automatically on scope exit via the generated destructor."
9:74 EOL "\n"
10:1 EOL "\n"
